1
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:15,880
In 1940, patriotic overseas Chinese Mr. Tan Kah Kee

2
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:19,000
led the Nanyang Comfort Delegation back to China to offer comfort.

3
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,800
After investigating in China,

4
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:22,600
he declared in Southeast Asia

5
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:24,520
that China's hope lies in Yan'an.

6
00:01:25,880 --> 00:01:28,800
Tan Kah Kee returned to China with the comfort delegation

7
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:30,130
and even went to Yan'an.

8
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:32,380
How did they get to Yan'an?

9
00:01:32,720 --> 00:01:33,880
By car, of course.

10
00:01:33,880 --> 00:01:35,200
By car?

11
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:36,000
Of course.

12
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:37,720
Otherwise, would you walk there?

13
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:40,680
I really doubt how you passed the exam to return to China.

14
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:41,320
Speaking of the exam,

15
00:01:41,320 --> 00:01:42,720
don't underestimate me.

16
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:46,240
During the exam, some people were scratching their heads

17
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:47,400
and looking extremely worried.

18
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,280
Some people

19
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,800
wrote lengthy essays.

20
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:50,320
I

21
00:01:50,320 --> 00:01:52,200
just patted my head

22
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:53,479
and came up with eight big characters.

23
00:01:53,479 --> 00:01:54,680
Guess what they were.

24
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:55,759
What were they?

25
00:01:55,759 --> 00:01:56,820
Eight characters?

26
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:57,840
Every man has a share of responsibility

27
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:59,370
for the fate of his country.

28
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:00,880
And you passed?

29
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:03,560
Before I returned,

30
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:05,360
my classmates left me a message:

31
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:06,760
Serve the motherland,

32
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:08,520
win glory for overseas Chinese,

33
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:10,840
the happiest and most glorious thing in the world

34
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:13,440
is to fight for the survival of our country.

35
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:15,920
There is hope.

36
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:19,160
It's good that there's hope.

37
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:20,640
Otherwise.

38
00:02:21,079 --> 00:02:21,880
Otherwise?

39
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:23,640
Otherwise what?

40
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:26,440
Otherwise, I would never

41
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:28,570
forgive myself for the rest of my life.

42
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:29,920
Tell me more

43
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:31,120
to break the boredom.

44
00:02:33,079 --> 00:02:34,210
Before coming back,

45
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:36,400
apart from driving and repairing cars,

46
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,920
I didn't have any other skills.

47
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:39,980
My family arranged a marriage for me.

48
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:42,440
The bride's family was also quite satisfied.

49
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:43,920
I thought

50
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:45,880
I would just get married, have kids,

51
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:47,140
and live a normal life.

52
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:49,170
Until I read the newspaper.

53
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:52,920
It called on Nanyang overseas Chinese mechanics to return and support the country.

54
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:56,380
China urgently needed people who could repair and drive cars.

55
00:02:56,640 --> 00:02:58,079
After reading the newspaper,

56
00:02:58,079 --> 00:02:59,680
I couldn't sleep for nights.

57
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,280
I kept thinking,

58
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:03,840
if I returned to China,

59
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:07,240
should I still get married?

60
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:11,040
If not, what if my parents disagreed?

61
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:13,370
But if I did get married,

62
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:15,360
what if I couldn't come back?

63
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:18,160
Wouldn't I be ruining her life?

64
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,160
So you sneaked back here?

65
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:26,920
Sneak back?

66
00:03:26,920 --> 00:03:28,640
A real man like me sneaking back?

67
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:30,100
I couldn't do such a thing.

68
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:33,120
Do you think everyone is like you?

69
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:36,240
At first, my parents disagreed,

70
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,370
saying war is cruel.

71
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:39,840
Besides, I had never fought in a war.

72
00:03:40,079 --> 00:03:43,440
But later, when they learned that hands were urgently needed to transport supplies,

73
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:45,040
they didn't stop me anymore.

74
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:46,880
The condition was

75
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:49,810
that I had to explain it clearly to the girl's family.

76
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,320
You're here.

77
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:21,399
Did something happen?

78
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:29,010
I'm going back to China.

79
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,480
Going back?

80
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:35,320
Are you going back to join the Resistance?

81
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:36,280
How did you know?

82
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,159
Look at these streets and alleys.

83
00:04:41,159 --> 00:04:42,320
Old and young,

84
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:45,530
who doesn't know the situation back home?

85
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:48,280
But

86
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:51,850
what can you do when you go back?

87
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:55,360
Be a driver and transport supplies.

88
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,120
But,

89
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:08,120
what about our marriage?

90
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:11,280
Our marriage,

91
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:18,560
can we still get married?

92
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:31,840
It's fine.

93
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:32,900
I will wait for you.

94
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:37,760
You wait for me.

95
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:41,010
Don't hold a grudge against me.

96
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:44,680
I don't know if I'll live or die once I go.

97
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:52,320
Let me go in and explain to your parents.

98
00:05:54,159 --> 00:05:55,680
I respect your choice.

99
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:57,480
I will explain it to my parents.

100
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:02,840
A true man sacrifices his life for his country,

101
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:04,440
and faces death fearlessly.

102
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:12,600
Brother doesn't smoke,

103
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:15,560
sister doesn't wear makeup,

104
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:18,920
save money to fight the Japanese.

105
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:21,840
Fight the Japanese!

106
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:24,720
Brothers and sisters, please donate some money.

107
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:25,960
Okay, wait.

108
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:36,760
Sister, this is too precious.

109
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:41,480
I didn't expect you to know the way to save the country at such a young age.

110
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:45,600
If I were tall enough,

111
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:48,060
I would have gone back to fight the Japanese.

112
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:53,760
It won't be too late to go back when you grow taller.

113
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:55,880
When I grow taller,

114
00:06:56,840 --> 00:06:59,560
the war will be over.

115
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:02,840
Wait.

116
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:07,920
Take this too.

117
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:10,700
But this is your dowry.

118
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:13,800
It's just some copper and iron.

119
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:16,360
Dowry.

120
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:18,280
Even though I can't go back,

121
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:20,200
we can save the country together.

122
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:26,080
What a broad mind.

123
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:30,200
Do what you must do.

124
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,280
Little Pushao.

125
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:35,320
I also have some words

126
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:36,980
that I haven't had time to say.

127
00:07:42,159 --> 00:07:44,560
If only there was no war.

128
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:46,440
But it happened anyway.

129
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:48,840
It seems that

130
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:51,500
what happened on the transport route

131
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,240
is far more thrilling

132
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:55,240
than I imagined before coming back.

133
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:57,159
However,

134
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:01,040
there is no dead end under the feet of a warrior.

135
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:03,040
These animals

136
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:03,920
killed our compatriots,

137
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:05,180
and invaded our China.

138
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:07,560
To stop us from transporting supplies,

139
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:10,440
they ran into the village and arrested mechanics everywhere.

140
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:11,440
And then?

141
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:13,520
Then to avoid capture,

142
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:16,850
we disguised ourselves under the cover of local villagers.

143
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,920
That's how we escaped.

144
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:21,640
As a result, one of us was unfortunately discovered.

145
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:23,280
To lure us out,

146
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:26,080
they even buried them alive right under our noses.

147
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:29,520
Those animals.

148
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,679
Now I only have one goal,

149
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:35,159
and that is to take revenge.

150
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:37,760
Even though I can't take up arms and go to the frontline,

151
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:40,080
every batch of supplies we transport

152
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:43,039
is preparing to send these demons to hell.

153
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,720
Calm down, brother.

154
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:47,450
They will get their retribution sooner or later.

155
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:52,040
History will eventually judge them.

156
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:58,440
Have any of you been to Yan'an?

157
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:04,040
I can drive all the way to Yan'an.

158
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:06,560
You were just asking where Yan'an is,

159
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:08,090
and now you can drive there.

160
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:11,960
It's getting late.

161
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,120
Since we have hope,

162
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,920
let's head towards it

163
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:16,200
and set off.

164
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:20,400
Attention, all overseas Chinese!

165
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:21,760
China will win!
